Gross Margin and

Contribution Margin


	 Calculate Foreman’s operating income if production and sales equal 
230,000 units. 

	 Selling Price = $2,600,000 / 200,000 = $13 

  Contribution Margin per Unit =

= Selling Price – Variable Cost

= $13 - $5.50 - $4.00

= $3.50


  Operating Income =

= UCM x quantity – Fixed Costs

= $3.50 x 230,000 - $500,000 - $350,000

= -$45,000


