Gross Margin and

Contribution Margin


  Why is Sam Hogan wrong? 
  He has interpreted gross margin as if it were all variable 
– in fact, GM per unit will increase to $5.33 (from $5) 
  He has interpreted marketing and distribution costs as
all fixed – in fact, total variable marketing costs will 
rise to $920k (from $800k) 
  Both the manufacturing costs and the marketing and
distribution costs contain fixed and variable 

components.


